stance of silently observing

250
00:14:05,110 --> 00:14:07,610
a battle between two men, that's fine.

251
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:09,780
But is that what you want?

252
00:14:14,610 --> 00:14:15,500
Tomo!

253
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:16,840
Wh-What?!

254
00:14:17,710 --> 00:14:20,290
I'm gonna challenge your dad today.

255
00:14:25,010 --> 00:14:28,970
Kashima Daimyojin

256
00:14:34,970 --> 00:14:37,180
Kashima Daimyojin

257
00:14:37,180 --> 00:14:37,980
Damn.

258
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:40,520
Jun-bo! What the hell are you thinking?!

259
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:43,970
You said you'd accept my challenge
at any time, didn't you?

260
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:47,030
So you will accept it, right?

261
00:14:47,030 --> 00:14:48,700
Very well, then.

262
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:53,450
I thought if I said that, you'd
give up on Tomo and run away.

263
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:56,290
I realize I'm at a huge disadvantage.

264
00:14:56,290 --> 00:15:00,670
So I'll do whatever I have to do to defeat you.

265
00:15:00,670 --> 00:15:02,080
And on that note...

266
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,510
I've called in some support.

267
00:15:04,510 --> 00:15:06,210
H-How dare you?!

268
00:15:06,210 --> 00:15:09,470
Br-Br-Bringing Akemi here is playing dirty!

269
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:12,090
Jun's challenging my dad right now.

270
00:15:12,090 --> 00:15:15,430
Should I really just stay here?

271
00:15:15,430 --> 00:15:20,640
Aizawa-san... If something's bothering you,
you can talk to me...

272
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:21,400
Huh?

273
00:15:23,230 --> 00:15:27,070
I see. So he really went to
challenge Goro-san, huh?

274
00:15:27,570 --> 00:15:29,360
Jun-kun's amazing.

275
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,780
You said it.

276
00:15:30,780 --> 00:15:35,740
Wait, Senpai, you knew Jun was
going to challenge my dad?

277
00:15:35,740 --> 00:15:40,460
Yeah, actually, he seemed stressed
about something over winter break,

278
00:15:40,460 --> 00:15:42,000
so I asked what was up, and...

279
00:15:42,420 --> 00:15:45,040
I know I don't have much chance of winning,

280
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:49,170
but I'm pretty sure this is
a battle I have to fight.

281
00:15:49,170 --> 00:15:52,970
So as long as Tomo doesn't abandon me, I...

282
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:56,060
"I can't give up," he said.

283
00:15:56,060 --> 00:15:59,600
Since he's such a sincere guy, I figured he
was fighting 'cause he thought he had to...

284
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:02,850
I think you should cheer Jun-kun on.

285
00:16:02,850 --> 00:16:05,060
I'm sure you know better than anyone...

286
00:16:06,190 --> 00:16:09,690
what would help him the most.

287
00:16:12,450 --> 00:16:14,110
Sorry, Senpai!

288
00:16:14,450 --> 00:16:16,330
I gotta leave early today!

289
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,250
Was that...

290
00:16:29,250 --> 00:16:31,920
Yeah, that wind pressure
was definitely Tomo.

291
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:35,140
Looks like she's over it. That's great.

292
00:16:35,140 --> 00:16:38,680
You're right. She must have had an epiphany.

293
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:46,860
Why don't you just give up already?

294
00:16:46,860 --> 00:16:49,440
You can't defeat me as you are now.

295
00:16:50,110 --> 00:16:52,990
Not... Not yet!

296
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:03,290
Hey, you okay? You're really wrecked.

297
00:17:03,290 --> 00:17:05,210
This is nothi—

298
00:17:05,210 --> 00:17:06,710
Wait, Tomo?!

299
00:17:06,710 --> 00:17:08,420
Wh-Why are you here?!

300
00:17:08,420 --> 00:17:10,960
Well, I was thinking about it.

301
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:13,050
You wanna go out with me, right?

302
00:17:13,050 --> 00:17:13,670
Huh?

303
00:17:13,670 --> 00:17:15,760
I wanna go out with you, too!

304
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:18,010
And the only one in the way of that...

305
00:17:18,430 --> 00:17:19,970
is my old man!

306
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:24,600
So it's fine if I defeat you instead, right?

307
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:26,190
What kind of logic is that?!

308
00:17:26,190 --> 00:17:28,480
This is between me and your dad!

309
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:30,480
I know, I know!

310
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:33,280
I'm not trying to show up in the
middle of your fight and butt in.

311
00:17:33,530 --> 00:17:36,660
But if you go down and can't get
back up, then it's my turn.

312
00:17:36,660 --> 00:17:39,990
And I'll beat him, so you can lose
without worrying about anything.

313
00:17:40,780 --> 00:17:43,870
Those eyes... She's serious.

314
00:17:44,830 --> 00:17:46,420
Oh, really?

315
00:17:46,790 --> 00:17:48,330
Well, now you've done it.

316
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:50,880
That's a hell of a lot of pressure!

317
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:54,470
Yo, Jun. I was watching for
a bit, and I think Dad...

318
00:17:54,470 --> 00:17:56,340
Yeah, I know.

319
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:01,600
I'd like one more round, please.

320
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:04,060
Hmph. You never learn.

321
00:18:04,810 --> 00:18:07,440
Something's different about him today.

322
00:18:07,810 --> 00:18:10,610
He's taking some wide swings
that leave him open.

323
00:18:10,980 --> 00:18:15,070
If he's doing that on purpose,
then what he's testing is...

324
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:20,160
There it is! A wide right!

325
00:18:20,570 --> 00:18:22,990
As often as he's doing it,
it's gotta be intentional.

326
00:18:22,990 --> 00:18:25,290
And if there's an opening,
I just have to take it!

327
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:27,290
It's as simple as that...

328
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:30,250
to say, at least!

329
00:18:30,790 --> 00:18:32,750
Kashima Daimyojin

330
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:37,420
I can't beat him with hit-and-away
strikes that have no momentum.

331
00:18:37,420 --> 00:18:40,260
I have to step right into his reach,
without thinking about consequences,

332
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:42,730
and deal a counter that uses
his own strength against him.

333
00:18:42,970 --> 00:18:46,310
That's probably what it's
gonna take to beat him.

334
00:18:48,390 --> 00:18:50,230
That's a real challenge for me.

335
00:18:51,020 --> 00:18:54,400
But it's a hurdle Tomo
could overcome easily.

336
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:56,400
That's probably the point of this test.

337
00:18:57,150 --> 00:19:01,320
Every day, somewhere in this world,
someone is unfairly getting hurt.

338
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:06,200
What if that happened
to someone close to me?

339
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:09,750
Tomo would act faster than anyone.

340
00:19:10,620 --> 00:19:12,920
If I hesitate for a second,
she'll be beyond my reach,

341
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:14,840
and I'll end up leaving her alone.

342
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:18,670
I get it, old man.

343
00:19:18,670 --> 00:19:21,680
That's why you're so worried
about her, isn't it?

344
00:19:22,050 --> 00:19:25,420
I'm sorry the man next to
her is someone like me.

345
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:28,480
Here I come!

346
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:29,520
Come.

347
00:19:32,020 --> 00:19:33,860
I'm not like Tomo.

348
00:19:34,570 --> 00:19:37,400
I can't put my life on the
line for a total stranger.

349
00:19:38,440 --> 00:19:40,780
The only one I could hope to do that for...

350
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:44,240
is the girl I love!

351
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:48,290
Go, Jun!

352
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:10,810
Jun... wo—

353
00:20:10,810 --> 00:20:13,060
Not enough!

354
00:20:13,060 --> 00:20:14,560
What?!

355
00:20:14,560 --> 00:20:16,770
Oh, enough already!

356
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:19,570
Huh?

357
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:21,740
It's true.

358
00:20:22,150 --> 00:20:26,780
For just a moment, my fingers
did touch the floor.

359
00:20:27,410 --> 00:20:30,370
You win, Junichiro.

360
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:36,500
I... I actually beat—

361
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:38,130
Yes!

362
00:20:38,130 --> 00:20:40,590
You won! You beat him!

363
00:20:41,220 --> 00:20:44,130
C'mon, Tomo, that hurts!

364
00:20:44,130 --> 00:20:45,340
Well done.

365
00:20:44,130 --> 00:20:46,220
You actually did it!

366
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:49,210
I give! I give!

367
00:20:51,140 --> 00:20:53,350
So you beat Dad, right?

368
00:20:53,850 --> 00:20:54,810
Yeah.

369
00:20:55,190 --> 00:20:58,520
Which means... it's okay now, right?

370
00:20:58,520 --> 00:21:00,690
Y'know, to go out with m—

371
00:21:00,690 --> 00:21:01,940
Wait!

372
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:05,910
I love you, Tomo! Please go out with me!

373
00:21:05,910 --> 00:21:06,740
Huh?

374
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:09,370
What?!

375
00:21:09,370 --> 00:21:12,450
I was about to say that!
Why'd you interrupt?!

376
00:21:12,450 --> 00:21:13,790
Why'd you have to say it?!

377
00:21:13,790 --> 00:21:16,040
It's the guy's job to say that, isn't it?

378
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:17,960
There's no law saying it has to be!

379
00:21:18,420 --> 00:21:21,090
If you're gonna do that, then I'm gonna...

380
00:21:31,510 --> 00:21:34,060
Wh-What did you just...

381
00:21:34,060 --> 00:21:35,660
You were amazing.

382
00:21:35,660 --> 00:21:36,760
Huh?

383
00:21:37,040 --> 00:21:41,240
When you beat my dad, you looked amazing.

384
00:21:41,830 --> 00:21:44,170
Watching you made my heart race.

385
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:45,870
But...

386
00:21:45,870 --> 00:21:47,540
You'd better be ready!

387
00:21:47,540 --> 00:21:53,090
From now on, I'm gonna be making
your heart race a lot more!

388
00:21:55,780 --> 00:21:58,040
I guess it's on, then.

389
00:22:01,070 --> 00:22:02,150
Yeah!

390
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:05,930
You'll never beat me!

391
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:14,560
(This suspicious behavior is...)

392
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:18,850
Hey, you know, I'm all mixed up

393
00:22:18,850 --> 00:22:23,320
It's too complicated, I'm freaking out

394
00:22:23,320 --> 00:22:25,860
I want to look cute to you

395
00:22:23,650 --> 00:22:29,200
(crazy, crazy, drive me crazy, and that's…)

396
00:22:25,860 --> 00:22:28,490
So I'm plotting, bargaining,
sly, and stubborn

397
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:32,990
Dizzying love

398
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:38,580
Just tell him to look at you

399
00:22:38,580 --> 00:22:43,550
And watch him stiffen up even more,
because you're both so awkward

400
00:22:43,550 --> 00:22:47,420
What? Even if we're alike in that way

401
00:22:47,420 --> 00:22:52,010
It doesn't make me happy, 'cause it
means our love is going nowhere

402
00:22:52,010 --> 00:23:00,900
Cloudy heart, swirling emotions—
I sense rain coming

403
00:23:00,900 --> 00:23:09,990
So I partly open my umbrella,
then sneakily scoot closer to you

404
00:23:09,990 --> 00:23:13,950
Please notice the curl of my
eyelashes as I keep blinking

405
00:23:13,950 --> 00:23:18,870
And don't say I'm acting weird

406
00:23:16,820 --> 00:23:20,950
One year ago, in spring, I confessed my love.

407
00:23:18,870 --> 00:23:22,840
All this plotting and bargaining
is my sly plan to look cute to you

408
00:23:21,870 --> 00:23:26,380
Without the support of everyone around me,
this love wouldn't have come to be.

409
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:27,880
Try to solve the riddle of
this soft, dizzying love

410
00:23:25,750 --> 00:23:30,010
(Buzzing, fidgeting)

411
00:23:28,510 --> 00:23:32,090
I, Aizawa Tomo, am now...

412
00:23:30,260 --> 00:23:34,810
Listen, I might be a bit
tangled in my own web now

413
00:23:33,550 --> 00:23:37,250
the happiest I could possibly be!

414
00:23:34,810 --> 00:23:38,850
But once you unravel the mystery,
you'll see pure lo-love
